robin.d:
robin1.N-COUNT 可数名词鸲;知更鸟 A robin is a small brown bird found in Europe. The male has an orangey-red neck and breast.
2.N-COUNT 可数名词鸫 A robin is a brown bird found in North America. The male has a reddish-brown breast. North American robins are larger than European ones, and are a completely different species of bird.
3.See also:round-robin;
